Coverage remained the same at 96.954% when pulling **d47e55a9be30d02e6483128f9cccb68cee023589 on issue_2639_rake_browse** into **1d3839cd35765b481b26aae4da0b119ce0a240d7 on main**.

Please be aware that this error has morphed, perhaps because we are now live with Alma? 

The most [recent instances reported in Honeybadger](https://app.honeybadger.io/projects/54399/faults/39793242) show:

```
NoMethodError: undefined method `errors' for #<Array:0x00007ff4e8af5098>
```
![Screen Shot 2021-08-09 at 10 57 03 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9905193/128727466-353ea956-ff98-476d-8862-647487a2e072.png)

[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/builds/42004874/badge)](https://coveralls.io/builds/42004874)

Coverage remained the same at 96.954% when pulling **ab3f314f20f541385addb602ea77bba5cc7936f1 on remove_ribbon_message** into **d8e3796728a5b61019068d680453b132a64a4551 on main**.
@kevinreiss can you update the spec?

The culprit is that the query submitted on the request ends with "()" and Blacklight is throwing an exception when trying to parse this query.

The URL in the Honeybadger report is 

```
https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog?utf8=%E2%9C%93&search_field=all_fields&q=Philipps+Payson+O%E2%80%99Brien%2C+How+the+War+Was+Won%3A+Air-Sea+Power+and+Allied+Victory+in+World+War+II+%28%29
```

When we decode the `q` parameter we get:

```
Philipps Payson O’Brien, How the War Was Won: Air-Sea Power and Allied Victory in World War II ()
```

Blacklight has some built-in error handling to deal with `Parslet` exceptions but it seems that this exception is not a `Parslet` exception per-se (although it happens in `Parslet`) and Blacklight is just letting the exception bubble all the way to the top.
